LU(w/o STI)-31
Oil Pressure Switch
LUBRICATION
6. Oil Pressure Switch
A: REMOVAL
CAUTION:
If the engine oil is spilt over exhaust pipe or the under cover, wipe it off with cloth to avoid emitting
smoke or causing a fire.
1) Disconnect the ground terminal from battery sensor. <Ref. to NT-5, BATTERY, NOTE, Note.>
2) Remove the rubber cap.
3) Disconnect the terminal from oil pressure switch.
LU-03194
LU-03195
15WRX_STI_US_EN.book 31
LU(w/o STI)-32
Oil Pressure Switch
LUBRICATION
4) Remove the oil pressure switch.
CAUTION:
Catch the engine oil using cloth to prevent it from splashing.
B: INSTALLATION
1) Apply liquid gasket to the oil pressure switch threads.
Liquid gasket:
THREE BOND 1324 (Part No. 004403042) or equivalent
LU-03196
LU-02743
15WRX_STI_US_EN.book 32
LU(w/o STI)-33
Oil Pressure Switch
LUBRICATION
2) Install the oil pressure switch to the chain cover.
Tightening torque:
18 Nm (1.8 kgf-m, 13.3 ft-lb)
3) Connect the terminal to the oil pressure switch.
NOTE:
The oil pressure switch harness must be tightened within the range of a 90 angle as shown below.
Tightening torque:
1.5 Nm (0.2 kgf-m, 1.1 ft-lb)
(A) Upper side of the engine

LU-03197
(A)
90

LU(w/o STI)-34
Oil Pressure Switch
LUBRICATION
4) Attach the rubber cap.
5) Connect the ground terminal to battery sensor. <Ref. to NT-5, BATTERY, NOTE, Note.>
C: INSPECTION
1) Check that the oil pressure switch does not have deformation, cracks or damage.
2) Check the oil pressure switch installation portion for oil leakage and oil seepage.
